; ding.ap: demonstrates the LCC+ `ding` trap.
; `ding` is an alias for `sound 0`: it plays the configured ding sound file,
; then falls back to a desktop default, then ASCII BEL (\x07).
; Run:  node src/plus/lccplus.js plusdemos/ding.ap
        .lccplus
        lea r0, msg
        sout r0
        nl
        ding            ; alias for sound 0
        halt
msg:    .string "ding.ap: playing the ding sound slot..."
